.header

.h1 Intro

Lesson 1: Every good work of software starts by scratching a developer's personal itch.

Without any claim that djedefre is a good work of software, my personal itch was
that I wanted a plot of my network as it was. I had seen Cheops in the past, and
that was the kind of network plot that I wanted. Cheops had developped into 
cheops-ng (next generation) and after that in abandonware. I tried in vain to 
compile cheops on an up-to-date ditribution.

So it was time for a successor. Not an newer-generation (ng-ng), but a successor.
The target is small networks (SOHO), for which the drawing will fit on 1 page. It
will use ssh to access managed systems to gather information. 
In addition, the relation with virtual machines should be clear and there must be
a status indicating whether a server is up or down.

The result would look like this:

.img network_example.png

The software is far from finished. Buttons don't have actions behind them et cetera.

